Fiat SpA &lt;FIAT.MI> declined to confirm ordeny an Italian newspaper report that it was studying thepossibility of issuing a convertible bond.    The Milan daily, Il Giornale, said a convertible bond issuewas under study but gave no details.    A Fiat spokesman contacted by Reuters said only that thereport was "one of the typical rumours which circulate on thebourse."    Senior sources at the Milan investment bank Sige, which IlGiornale said was involved in the planning along withMediobanca - Banca di Credito Finanziario SpA and IMI -Istituto Mobiliare Italiano, said they were unaware of any suchproject. REUTER&#3;